<section id="talker">

    <p class="text-danger unsupported hidden">
        Ack! looks like this browser isn't supported :( Unfortunately, you will currently have to try with either Safari or Chrome until Mozilla adds further speechSynthesis support to Firefox.
    </p>

    <p>
        Text to Speech! HTML5 is just the best. Enter some text in the box and hit <span class="text-success"><strong>play</strong></span> to listen to it.
    </p>

    <textarea class="form-control" rows="3" name="talkerText">Try me! Just press "Play"</textarea>

    <div class="button-wrapper">
        <button class="btn btn-large btn-success play">
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-play"></span> Play!
        </button>
        <button class="btn btn-large btn-danger cancel" disabled>
            <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-stop"></span> Stop the madness!
        </button>
        <div class="throbber hidden">
            Loading...
        </div>
    </div>

        <p class="text-info">
            Click on any of the voices to try them:
        </p>

        <ul id="voice-list">
            <% for(var i=0; i < voices.length; i++) { %>
                <li class="voice-li" data-voice="<%= voices[i].name %>"><%= voices[i].name %></li>
            <% } %>
        </ul>

    <p class="bg-warning">
        Note: sometimes it seems to stop working, and only resumes working if you restart the browser. Not sure why yet.
    </p>

</section>
